sentences: Francisco Ismael Segundo Parraguez Cabezas, or simply Ismael Parraguez (1883—8 May 1917) was a Chilean musician, Normal teacher, poet, and novelist.

He was known for being the creator of the Orfeón Chileno in 1914, during the centennial of the Battle of Rancagua and the children's poem Los pollitos dicen, which he published on his 1907 book Poesías Infantiles.

Francisco Ismael Segundo was born on 26 August 1883, at Fundo Las Pataguas in Pichidegua, Colchagua province, in central Chile.
He graduated there in 1899 as a normal teacher.
He published his first book, Un idilio menos, in 1903, which soon went out of stock.
It was followed by Poesías infantiles some years later, in 1907.

Ismael Parraguez died unexpectedly aged 33 on 8 May 1917 in Santiago.
